         <p class="- topic/p ">An LCM reminder can be temporarily removed from the
display by the user by pressing the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol> key
to acknowledge the alarm, but after a defined period (default is set
to 30 days) the pop-up message will reappear. After a configured amount
of repeats (default is set to 3 times), the pop-up will not reoccur.
Final acknowledgement and timer restart can only be performed by an
FSR.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Common Alarm</uicontrol> LED is blinking
(0.5s ON, 0.5s OFF...) and the buzzer is activated when an LCM reminder
pop-up message is shown on the display. </p>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Setting Sheet</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">All configuration parameters
of the LCM functionality are stored in the setting sheet. The parameters
are set to default values and normally require no modification during
system configuration.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The LCM module also stores its counters’
status information in a setting. This value requires no modification.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To modify the LCM configuration parameters, see <xref href="Service_Serviceport_LCM_Status_Menu_REF_0000116555.dita"
